    article: ["Understanding the concept of squaring negative numbers has practical applications in various fields of mathematics, science, and engineering. It plays a role in solving equations, analyzing data, and modeling physical phenomena. For instance, in physics, when calculating distances, velocities, or accelerations, squaring negative values may be necessary to obtain meaningful results.", "In mathematics, (-2) squared is indeed 4, not -4. Squaring a negative number negates its negativity, resulting in a positive value. This concept is consistent with the rules of mathematics and serves as a foundation for various mathematical and scientific applications.Calculus introduces the notion of infinity, which can be baffling. Dealing with limits, infinite series, and infinite processes can feel counterintuitive and lead to confusion.", "The next time you encounter the question of what happens when you square a negative number, remember that the outcome is positive—a testament to the elegant simplicity of mathematical principles."]
