    article: ["Motivation acts as a driving force that fuels a student's desire to learn and improve. In remote learning settings, where direct supervision may be limited, self-motivation becomes even more critical. Here's how students can boost their motivation", "a) Find Personal Relevance: Help students understand the practical applications and real-world significance of higher-level math concepts. When students see the relevance of what they're learning, they are more likely to stay engaged and motivated", "b) Celebrate Progress: Recognize and celebrate the milestones achieved during the learning journey. Acknowledging progress, no matter how small, reinforces a sense of accomplishment and encourages further effort", "c) Seek Support and Collaboration: Encourage students to connect with peers and teachers through virtual platforms. Group discussions and collaborative problem-solving can foster a sense of community and mutual support", "Effective self-study habits are the foundation of any successful remote learner. Students must take ownership of their learning journey and actively engage with the material. Here are some strategies to develop self-study habits", "If you’re a motivated student, remote learning can work magic!"]
