            {
                title: "Abstraction Overload",
                article: [
                    "Calculus introduces students to a new level of abstraction, which can be overwhelming. Unlike algebra or geometry, calculus often deals with concepts that can't be visualized as easily. Concepts like limits, derivatives, and integrals operate in the realm of the abstract, requiring a shift in thinking.",
                ],
